{"parentUuid":null,"isSidechain":true,"promptId":"8f669a5b-43d8-4540-b4e8-5b6a0a5d209a","agentId":"aef50341d109baea0","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":"Research Carl Jung's Bollingen Tower (the Tower / \"Turm\" at Bollingen on Lake Zurich) and his concept of individuation, then design how to use it as the spine of a serious-but-fun apprenticeship/bootcamp for mastering algorithms and mathematics.\n\nFirst, get the real details (use web search/fetch — you can load tools via ToolSearch with query \"select:WebSearch,WebFetch\"):\n- The actual history: Jung built it by hand in stone starting 1923, added towers/wings over ~30+ years, each addition reflecting a stage of his psychological development; deliberately primitive — no electricity, drew water by hand, chopped wood; a place of solitude, retreat, dreams, and deep inner work; he carved stone reliefs and inscriptions.\n- The psychology: individuation (becoming who you truly are by integrating the unconscious), the Tower as a \"confession in stone\" and a concretization of the psyche, solitude as generative, the slow accretion over decades.\n\nThen design a reusable thematic frame mapping this onto a year-long deep-study bootcamp:\n- \"The Tower\" = the learner's deep-work sanctuary (physical desk/space ritual + the growing edifice of mastered knowledge). Each mastered data structure / proof / paper = a stone laid; each curriculum phase = a new wing/storey added.\n- Solitude and primitiveness = deep-work / distraction-free ritual (no phone, analog notebook, the \"no electricity\" ethos as focus discipline).\n- Individuation = the real goal: not passing interviews, but becoming a person who thinks like a scientist — integrating knowledge until it's part of you (\"derive don't memorize\").\n- Carving inscriptions = keeping a proof notebook / lab journal; the slow stone-by-stone accretion = consistency over a year.\n- A short, genuinely evocative opening passage addressed to the apprentice about beginning to build their Tower.\n\nKeep it serious, literary, and motivating — not cheesy. Map every poetic element to a concrete real study habit. Return a tight markdown design note (the history, the mapping table, and the opening passage) that can be folded into a study-plan document as its framing spine."},"uuid":"f093654d-774d-4528-87d6-8dedef213616","timestamp":"2026-06-17T18:32:05.784Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/riz/git/dotfiles","sessionId":"2cde58bf-2f4b-4d9c-ade9-87cc9f7b1872","version":"2.1.179","gitBranch":"main","slug":"snappy-stargazing-quasar"}
