{"parentUuid":"f1869806-1eea-4efb-afa1-d46f15d00154","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aef50341d109baea0","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01NusGXTZ2fgfjbKjWpofhQq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01JU96SC95vGWQavS8Az9v9D","name":"WebSearch","input":{"query":"Carl Jung Bollingen Tower history built 1923 stone individuation confession in stone"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":743,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13602,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":13602,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":48,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":{"cache_miss_reason":{"type":"tools_changed","cache_missed_input_tokens":7745}}},"requestId":"req_011Cc9JwuweZYGMEzfqbdjgV","attributionAgent":"general-purpose","type":"assistant","uuid":"87c556d9-9041-4faf-9df1-dc9d2466003f","timestamp":"2026-06-17T18:32:10.742Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/riz/git/dotfiles","sessionId":"2cde58bf-2f4b-4d9c-ade9-87cc9f7b1872","version":"2.1.179","gitBranch":"main","slug":"snappy-stargazing-quasar"}
{"parentUuid":"87c556d9-9041-4faf-9df1-dc9d2466003f","isSidechain":true,"agentId":"aef50341d109baea0","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_01NusGXTZ2fgfjbKjWpofhQq","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01QscZCpWThV3aVBkAdUPYSC","name":"WebSearch","input":{"query":"Jung Bollingen Tower additions stages of psychological development no electricity solitude inscriptions stone reliefs"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":743,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13602,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":13602,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0},"output_tokens":48,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":{"cache_miss_reason":{"type":"tools_changed","cache_missed_input_tokens":7745}}},"requestId":"req_011Cc9JwuweZYGMEzfqbdjgV","attributionAgent":"general-purpose","type":"assistant","uuid":"bdfbd5da-89fa-40c9-9b1c-aa834c3e3891","timestamp":"2026-06-17T18:32:11.495Z","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/riz/git/dotfiles","sessionId":"2cde58bf-2f4b-4d9c-ade9-87cc9f7b1872","version":"2.1.179","gitBranch":"main","slug":"snappy-stargazing-quasar"}
{"parentUuid":"87c556d9-9041-4faf-9df1-dc9d2466003f","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"8f669a5b-43d8-4540-b4e8-5b6a0a5d209a","agentId":"aef50341d109baea0","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01JU96SC95vGWQavS8Az9v9D","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Carl Jung Bollingen Tower history built 1923 stone individuation confession in stone\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Bollingen Tower\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bollingen_Tower\"},{\"title\":\"C. G. Jung House Museum\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C._G._Jung_House_Museum\"},{\"title\":\"Bollingen\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bollingen\"},{\"title\":\"Carl Jung\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carl_Jung\"},{\"title\":\"Carl Alfred Meier\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carl_Alfred_Meier\"}]\n\nBased on the search results, here's what I found about Carl Jung's Bollingen Tower:\n\n## History and Construction\n\nJung bought the land in 1922 after the death of his mother, and in 1923 he built a two-storey round tower on this land. It was a stone structure suitable to be lived in. Additions to this tower were constructed in 1927, 1931, and 1935, resulting in a building that has four connected parts.\n\n## Significance and Symbolism\n\nIn appearance, it is a small castle with four towers, located in the village of Bollingen on the shore of the Obersee (upper lake) basin of Lake Zürich. For much of his life Jung spent several months each year living at Bollingen.\n\n## Stone Inscriptions\n\nIn 1950, on the occasion of his 75th birthday, Jung set up a stone cube on the lakeshore, just west of the tower, inscribing it on three sides. This stone cube contained meaningful inscriptions, including a philosophical quote about the value of humble things.\n\nThe Bollingen Tower remains an important testament to Jung's psychological work and personal philosophy, though the Tower is now owned by a family trust and is not open to the public.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"4d4f96a8-f1d6-488d-b544-c856b7a1e834","timestamp":"2026-06-17T18:32:20.337Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"Carl Jung Bollingen Tower history built 1923 stone individuation confession in stone","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_019WcnweQMnhzHP1xg39crJx","content":[{"title":"Bollingen Tower","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bollingen_Tower"},{"title":"C. G. Jung House Museum","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/C._G._Jung_House_Museum"},{"title":"Bollingen","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bollingen"},{"title":"Carl Jung","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carl_Jung"},{"title":"Carl Alfred Meier","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carl_Alfred_Meier"}]},"Based on the search results, here's what I found about Carl Jung's Bollingen Tower:\n\n## History and Construction\n\nJung bought the land in 1922 after the death of his mother, and in 1923 he built a two-storey round tower on this land. It was a stone structure suitable to be lived in. Additions to this tower were constructed in 1927, 1931, and 1935, resulting in a building that has four connected parts.\n\n## Significance and Symbolism\n\nIn appearance, it is a small castle with four towers, located in the village of Bollingen on the shore of the Obersee (upper lake) basin of Lake Zürich. For much of his life Jung spent several months each year living at Bollingen.\n\n## Stone Inscriptions\n\nIn 1950, on the occasion of his 75th birthday, Jung set up a stone cube on the lakeshore, just west of the tower, inscribing it on three sides. This stone cube contained meaningful inscriptions, including a philosophical quote about the value of humble things.\n\nThe Bollingen Tower remains an important testament to Jung's psychological work and personal philosophy, though the Tower is now owned by a family trust and is not open to the public."],"durationSeconds":9.594346374999994,"searchCount":1},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"87c556d9-9041-4faf-9df1-dc9d2466003f","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/riz/git/dotfiles","sessionId":"2cde58bf-2f4b-4d9c-ade9-87cc9f7b1872","version":"2.1.179","gitBranch":"main","slug":"snappy-stargazing-quasar"}
{"parentUuid":"bdfbd5da-89fa-40c9-9b1c-aa834c3e3891","isSidechain":true,"promptId":"60c52c46-5540-4aa1-b243-4375383b64a7","agentId":"aef50341d109baea0","type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"tool_use_id":"toolu_01QscZCpWThV3aVBkAdUPYSC","type":"tool_result","content":"Web search results for query: \"Jung Bollingen Tower additions stages of psychological development no electricity solitude inscriptions stone reliefs\"\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Modern Man in Search of a Soul\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Modern_Man_in_Search_of_a_Soul\"},{\"title\":\"Bollingen (disambiguation)\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bollingen_(disambiguation)\"},{\"title\":\"Analytical psychology\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Analytical_psychology\"},{\"title\":\"The Collected Works of C. G. Jung\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Collected_Works_of_C._G._Jung\"},{\"title\":\"Carl Jung\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carl_Jung\"},{\"title\":\"Nigredo\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nigredo\"},{\"title\":\"Anima and animus\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anima_and_animus\"},{\"title\":\"The Origins and History of Consciousness\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Origins_and_History_of_Consciousness\"},{\"title\":\"Psychology and Alchemy\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Psychology_and_Alchemy\"}]\n\nLet me search more specifically for information about the Bollingen Tower itself:\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Bollingen Tower\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bollingen_Tower\"},{\"title\":\"Bollingen Foundation\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bollingen_Foundation\"},{\"title\":\"Bollingen\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bollingen\"},{\"title\":\"Montaigne%27s tower\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Montaigne%27s_tower\"},{\"title\":\"The Collected Works of C. G. Jung\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Collected_Works_of_C._G._Jung\"}]\n\nLet me search for more specific information about the tower's lack of electricity and its symbolic design:\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Bollingen (disambiguation)\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bollingen_(disambiguation)\"},{\"title\":\"Psychology and Alchemy\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Psychology_and_Alchemy\"},{\"title\":\"Bollingen\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bollingen\"},{\"title\":\"Man and His Symbols\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Man_and_His_Symbols\"},{\"title\":\"Black Books (Jung)\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Black_Books_(Jung)\"},{\"title\":\"Victor White (priest)\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Victor_White_(priest)\"},{\"title\":\"The Collected Works of C. G. Jung\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Collected_Works_of_C._G._Jung\"}]\n\nLet me search more specifically for information about the stone reliefs and symbolic inscriptions on the tower:\n\nLinks: [{\"title\":\"Bollingen Tower\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bollingen_Tower\"},{\"title\":\"Bollingen (disambiguation)\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bollingen_(disambiguation)\"},{\"title\":\"Psychology and Alchemy\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Psychology_and_Alchemy\"},{\"title\":\"Rock carvings in Central Norway\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rock_carvings_in_Central_Norway\"},{\"title\":\"Man and His Symbols\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Man_and_His_Symbols\"},{\"title\":\"Collective unconscious\",\"url\":\"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Collective_unconscious\"}]\n\nBased on the search results I've retrieved, here's what I found about the Bollingen Tower:\n\n## The Bollingen Tower\n\nThe Bollingen Tower is a structure built by Swiss psychiatrist Carl Jung. In appearance, it is a small castle with four towers. It is located in the village of Bollingen on the shore of the Obersee (upper lake) basin of Lake Zürich.\n\n### Construction and Additions\n\nJung bought the land in 1922 after the death of his mother. In 1923 he built a two-storey round tower on this land. Additions to this tower were constructed in 1927, 1931, and 1935, resulting in a building that has four connected parts. A second storey was added to the 1927 addition after the death of Jung's wife in 1955, signifying \"an extension of consciousness achieved in old age.\"\n\n### Inscriptions and Stone Monuments\n\nIn 1950, on the occasion of his 75th birthday, Jung set up a stone cube on the lakeshore, just west of the tower, inscribing it on three sides. One side contains a quote taken from the Rosarium philosophorum: \"Here stands the mean, uncomely stone, 'Tis very cheap in price! The more it is despised by fools, The more loved by the wise.\"\n\n### Living at Bollingen\n\nFor much of his life Jung spent several months each year living at Bollingen.\n\nUnfortunately, the search results do not contain detailed information about the tower's lack of electricity, stone reliefs with specific symbolic content, or how the successive additions relate to specific stages of psychological development. To fully address those aspects of your query, additional sources would be needed.\n\n\nREMINDER: You MUST include the sources above in your response to the user using markdown hyperlinks."}]},"uuid":"dff5a5cb-06d3-4b2f-8cf8-29650a938472","timestamp":"2026-06-17T18:32:46.258Z","toolUseResult":{"query":"Jung Bollingen Tower additions stages of psychological development no electricity solitude inscriptions stone reliefs","results":[{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01T8YoxawTr3Yha5xYn36F3j","content":[{"title":"Modern Man in Search of a Soul","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Modern_Man_in_Search_of_a_Soul"},{"title":"Bollingen (disambiguation)","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bollingen_(disambiguation)"},{"title":"Analytical psychology","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Analytical_psychology"},{"title":"The Collected Works of C. G. Jung","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Collected_Works_of_C._G._Jung"},{"title":"Carl Jung","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Carl_Jung"},{"title":"Nigredo","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Nigredo"},{"title":"Anima and animus","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Anima_and_animus"},{"title":"The Origins and History of Consciousness","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Origins_and_History_of_Consciousness"},{"title":"Psychology and Alchemy","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Psychology_and_Alchemy"}]},"Let me search more specifically for information about the Bollingen Tower itself:",{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01ThwERT6MDLLBFJqUKs1r84","content":[{"title":"Bollingen Tower","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bollingen_Tower"},{"title":"Bollingen Foundation","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bollingen_Foundation"},{"title":"Bollingen","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bollingen"},{"title":"Montaigne%27s tower","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Montaigne%27s_tower"},{"title":"The Collected Works of C. G. Jung","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Collected_Works_of_C._G._Jung"}]},"Let me search for more specific information about the tower's lack of electricity and its symbolic design:",{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_016VTxCyYcZn6ddT43Gs5zWC","content":[{"title":"Bollingen (disambiguation)","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bollingen_(disambiguation)"},{"title":"Psychology and Alchemy","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Psychology_and_Alchemy"},{"title":"Bollingen","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bollingen"},{"title":"Man and His Symbols","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Man_and_His_Symbols"},{"title":"Black Books (Jung)","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Black_Books_(Jung)"},{"title":"Victor White (priest)","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Victor_White_(priest)"},{"title":"The Collected Works of C. G. Jung","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Collected_Works_of_C._G._Jung"}]},"Let me search more specifically for information about the stone reliefs and symbolic inscriptions on the tower:",{"tool_use_id":"srvtoolu_01CDgzukggV2BHEM746J3z2j","content":[{"title":"Bollingen Tower","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bollingen_Tower"},{"title":"Bollingen (disambiguation)","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Bollingen_(disambiguation)"},{"title":"Psychology and Alchemy","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Psychology_and_Alchemy"},{"title":"Rock carvings in Central Norway","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Rock_carvings_in_Central_Norway"},{"title":"Man and His Symbols","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Man_and_His_Symbols"},{"title":"Collective unconscious","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Collective_unconscious"}]},"Based on the search results I've retrieved, here's what I found about the Bollingen Tower:\n\n## The Bollingen Tower\n\nThe Bollingen Tower is a structure built by Swiss psychiatrist Carl Jung. In appearance, it is a small castle with four towers. It is located in the village of Bollingen on the shore of the Obersee (upper lake) basin of Lake Zürich.\n\n### Construction and Additions\n\nJung bought the land in 1922 after the death of his mother. In 1923 he built a two-storey round tower on this land. Additions to this tower were constructed in 1927, 1931, and 1935, resulting in a building that has four connected parts. A second storey was added to the 1927 addition after the death of Jung's wife in 1955, signifying \"an extension of consciousness achieved in old age.\"\n\n### Inscriptions and Stone Monuments\n\nIn 1950, on the occasion of his 75th birthday, Jung set up a stone cube on the lakeshore, just west of the tower, inscribing it on three sides. One side contains a quote taken from the Rosarium philosophorum: \"Here stands the mean, uncomely stone, 'Tis very cheap in price! The more it is despised by fools, The more loved by the wise.\"\n\n### Living at Bollingen\n\nFor much of his life Jung spent several months each year living at Bollingen.\n\nUnfortunately, the search results do not contain detailed information about the tower's lack of electricity, stone reliefs with specific symbolic content, or how the successive additions relate to specific stages of psychological development. To fully address those aspects of your query, additional sources would be needed."],"durationSeconds":34.76186275,"searchCount":4},"sourceToolAssistantUUID":"bdfbd5da-89fa-40c9-9b1c-aa834c3e3891","userType":"external","entrypoint":"cli","cwd":"/Users/riz/git/dotfiles","sessionId":"2cde58bf-2f4b-4d9c-ade9-87cc9f7b1872","version":"2.1.179","gitBranch":"main","slug":"snappy-stargazing-quasar"}
